<?xml version='1.0' standalone='yes'?>
<!DOCTYPE PLUGIN [
<!ENTITY name      "borg-backup-ui">
<!ENTITY author    "Thorsten Steinberg">
<!ENTITY version   "2026.06.29.2324">
<!ENTITY github    "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/borgforge/borg-backup-ui">
<!ENTITY pluginURL "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/borgforge/borg-backup-ui/test-channel/&name;-test.plg">
<!ENTITY bootdir   "/boot/config/plugins/&name;">
<!ENTITY pkgurl    "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/borgforge/borg-backup-ui/test-channel/releases/&name;-&version;.txz">
]>

<PLUGIN name="&name;"
        author="&author;"
        version="&version;"
        pluginURL="&pluginURL;"
        description="TEST CHANNEL - Web UI for Borg Backup. Install this only on test systems."
        icon="plugin-icon.png">

<CHANGES>
<![CDATA[
###2026.06.29.2324###
- Issue #92:
  - Backup overdue reminders now support weekday cron ranges and lists such as 0 9 * * 1-5.

###2026.06.29.2248###
- Issue #92:
  - Applied startup migrations are now written to migrations.log.jsonl so the latest migration summary shows the correct run time and actions.

###2026.06.29.2235###
- Issue #92:
  - System health now shows recorded startup migrations such as notification event migration with status, changed keys and execution time.

###2026.06.29.2151###
- Issue #92:
  - Notification delivery now uses a central event dispatcher for Unraid notifications, email and ntfy.
  - Settings now allow channel-specific event selection and a reminder interval for overdue restore-test notifications.
  - Scheduled restore-test overdue reminders are rate-limited and survive UI restarts.

###2026.06.29.1933###
- Issue #98:
  - Dashboard job icons now use the configured job metadata, matching the Jobs page.

###2026.06.29.1813###
- Issue #93:
  - Restore History delete buttons now use a less prominent outline style.

###2026.06.29.1738###
- Issue #93:
  - Restore History now keeps completed restore runs as individual records and allows deleting history entries from the UI.

###2026.06.29.1704###
- Issue #93:
  - Restore History migration state now records central registry no-op results correctly after earlier migration attempts.

###2026.06.29.1626###
- Issue #93:
  - Restore History migration now runs through the central migration registry instead of restore_api.
  - Obsolete restore-history-internal migration tracking files are cleaned up; central migration-state.json remains authoritative.

###2026.06.29.1544###
- Issue #93:
  - Restore History migration now skips legacy restore-run entries that were already imported by restore ID.

###2026.06.29.1502###
- Issue #93:
  - Startup checks no longer overwrite the last effective migration timestamp when no migration work is required.

###2026.06.29.1442###
- Issue #93:
  - Restore History view now uses clearer tabs, colored status badges, restore IDs and collapsible details.
  - Legacy restore history entries with empty conflict mode now show the effective default conflict strategy.

###2026.06.29.1402###
- Issue #93:
  - Restore History is now opened as a separate Browse & Restore view instead of being shown above the wizard.
  - Restore History migration is reported through the central startup migration state shown under Settings.

###2026.06.29.1336###
- Issue #93:
  - Browse & Restore now includes a dedicated Restore History with structured details for completed restore runs.
  - Existing completed entries from restore-runs.json are migrated once into the new restore-history storage with an audit log.

###2026.06.29.1048###
- Issue #90:
  - Resuming an active restore now opens a dedicated live-log mode instead of rerunning the wizard precheck.

###2026.06.29.1010###
- Issue #90:
  - Restore page now only shows active restore runs in the wizard; completed restore history is tracked separately.

###2026.06.29.0908###
- Issue #90:
  - Restore page keeps running restores visible but shows completed restore runs only as a compact limited history.

###2026.06.29.0853###
- Issue #90:
  - Active UI sessions are refreshed during restore activity so long-running restores do not sign out active users.
  - Restore page now shows recent restore runs and can resume a running restore live log after reload or re-login.

###2026.06.28.1750###
- Fixed the edit wizard so existing job metadata repository and source paths are shown instead of legacy backup.conf defaults.

###2026.06.28.1718###
- Issue #87:
  - Added ntfy events for scheduled restore test success, failure and overdue detection.

###2026.06.28.1624###
- Issue #87:
  - Added ntfy push notifications with test delivery and selectable backup success, failure and skipped events.
  - ntfy passwords and access tokens are stored as secret files and are not written to backup.conf.

###2026.06.28.0956###
- Issue #82:
  - Job start confirmation now shows whether all or only selected Docker containers and VMs will be stopped.

###2026.06.27.1921###
- Issue #82:
  - Wizard now separates Docker and VM runtime selection into dedicated optional steps.

###2026.06.27.1847###
- Issue #82:
  - Wizard runtime selection is wider, shows readable status badges and lists selected runtime targets in the preview.
  - Selective Docker logs now show only the selected containers.

###2026.06.27.1831###
- Issue #82:
  - Appdata and VM domain risk confirmations are only required when the full standard directory is selected.

###2026.06.27.1821###
- Issue #82:
  - Wizard runtime selection now uses a dedicated step with clearer Docker and VM choices.
  - Docker container discovery for the wizard is more compatible with Unraid systems.

###2026.06.27.1751###
- Issue #82:
  - Wizard can stop all or selected Docker containers and VMs before a backup.
  - Appdata and VM domain source paths now show explicit risk acknowledgements when not all related runtime services are stopped.

###2026.06.26.1347###
- Release (#35):
  - Einheitliches Redesign fuer Dashboard, Jobs, History, Berichte, Restore Tests, Browse & Restore, Storage, Einstellungen und Hilfe.
  - Profilbasierte Speicherziele, SMTP/Wochenbericht, Import/Export und Plugin-Installationspruefungen enthalten die getesteten Korrekturen.

###2026.06.15.1213###
- Aktueller Stand (#60):
  - Wochenbericht zeigt die Erfolgsquote der letzten 7 Tage statt der historischen Gesamtquote.
  - Wochenbericht enthaelt den aktuellen Mailkopf, sortierte Job-Uebersicht und fokussierte Log-Hinweise.
  - Restore-Test-Berichte und Plugin-UI entsprechen dem aktuellen stabilen Unraid-Plugin-Stand.
  - Vollstaendige technische Historie wurde nach docs/changelog.md ausgelagert.
]]>
</CHANGES>

<!--
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Step 1 – Download and install the plugin package
  The .txz contains:
    /boot/config/plugins/borg-backup-ui/      → App files (persistent on flash)
    /etc/rc.d/rc.borg_backup_ui               → Start/stop script
    /usr/local/emhttp/plugins/borg-backup-ui/ → Unraid plugin metadata
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-->
<FILE Name="&bootdir;/&name;-&version;.txz" Run="upgradepkg --install-new">
<URL>&pkgurl;</URL>
<MD5>332453a55f1062b4869804d36a88df1d</MD5>
</FILE>

<!--
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Step 2 – Post-install: autostart + initial launch
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-->
<FILE Name="/tmp/borg-backup-ui-install.sh" Run="/bin/bash">
<INLINE>
#!/bin/bash
PLUGIN_DIR="/boot/config/plugins/borg-backup-ui"
PACKAGE_FILE="${PLUGIN_DIR}/borg-backup-ui-&version;.txz"
GO_FILE="/boot/config/go"

# Defensive fallback: some Unraid/plugin-manager upgradepkg runs may finish
# without leaving the package payload in /boot/config/plugins/borg-backup-ui.
if [ ! -f "${PLUGIN_DIR}/borg_backup_ui.py" ]; then
  if [ -f "${PACKAGE_FILE}" ]; then
    echo "Plugin payload missing after upgradepkg; extracting package fallback."
    tar -xf "${PACKAGE_FILE}" -C / 2>/tmp/borg-backup-ui-install-extract.err || true
  fi
fi

if [ ! -f "${PLUGIN_DIR}/borg_backup_ui.py" ]; then
  echo "ERROR: borg-backup-ui payload was not installed from ${PACKAGE_FILE}."
  if [ -s /tmp/borg-backup-ui-install-extract.err ]; then
    cat /tmp/borg-backup-ui-install-extract.err
  fi
  exit 1
fi

# Create default config if none exists yet
if [ ! -f "${PLUGIN_DIR}/borg_backup_ui.conf" ]; then
  cp "${PLUGIN_DIR}/borg_backup_ui.conf.example" \
     "${PLUGIN_DIR}/borg_backup_ui.conf" 2>/dev/null || true
  echo "Created borg_backup_ui.conf from template."
fi

# Register autostart in /boot/config/go (once)
if ! grep -q "rc.borg_backup_ui" "${GO_FILE}" 2>/dev/null; then
  echo ""                                    >> "${GO_FILE}"
  echo "# Borg Backup UI"                   >> "${GO_FILE}"
  echo "/etc/rc.d/rc.borg_backup_ui start"  >> "${GO_FILE}"
  echo "Autostart registered in ${GO_FILE}."
fi

# Copy restore-test script to scripts/ (if phase-1 migration was done)
# Bootstrap borg-backup runtime directories
BORG_BASE="/boot/config/borg-backup"
mkdir -p "${BORG_BASE}/config/jobs" "${BORG_BASE}/locks" "${BORG_BASE}/scripts"

# Legacy cleanup: old external runtime lib is no longer used.
if [ -d "${BORG_BASE}/lib" ]; then
  rm -rf "${BORG_BASE}/lib" 2>/dev/null || true
fi

# Copy standalone backup.conf.example into runtime config path
cp -f "${PLUGIN_DIR}/runtime/config/backup.conf.example" "${BORG_BASE}/config/backup.conf.example" 2>/dev/null || true
if [ ! -f "${BORG_BASE}/config/backup.conf" ]; then
  cp -f "${BORG_BASE}/config/backup.conf.example" "${BORG_BASE}/config/backup.conf" 2>/dev/null || true
fi

# Copy restore-test script into runtime scripts path
cp -f "${PLUGIN_DIR}/runtime/scripts/borg_restore_test.py"          "${BORG_BASE}/scripts/" 2>/dev/null || true
cp -f "${PLUGIN_DIR}/runtime/scripts/borg_restore_test.description" "${BORG_BASE}/scripts/" 2>/dev/null || true

# Stop any running instance, then start fresh
/etc/rc.d/rc.borg_backup_ui stop 2>/dev/null || true
sleep 1
/etc/rc.d/rc.borg_backup_ui start

# Cleanup local release artifacts: keep current + previous, delete older ones
RELEASE_DIR="${PLUGIN_DIR}"
if [ -d "${RELEASE_DIR}" ]; then
  _keep=0
  ls -1t "${RELEASE_DIR}"/borg-backup-ui-*.txz 2>/dev/null | while IFS= read -r _old; do
    _keep=$((_keep + 1))
    if [ "${_keep}" -gt 2 ]; then
      rm -f "${_old}" 2>/dev/null || true
    fi
  done
fi

rm -f /tmp/borg-backup-ui-install.sh
rm -f /tmp/borg-backup-ui-install-extract.err
</INLINE>
</FILE>

<FILE Name="/tmp/borg-backup-ui-remove.sh" Run="/bin/bash" Method="remove">
<INLINE>
#!/bin/bash
GO_FILE="/boot/config/go"

# Stop the service
/etc/rc.d/rc.borg_backup_ui stop 2>/dev/null || true

# Remove autostart from /boot/config/go
sed -i '/# Borg Backup UI/d' "${GO_FILE}" 2>/dev/null || true
sed -i '/rc.borg_backup_ui/d' "${GO_FILE}" 2>/dev/null || true

rm -f /tmp/borg-backup-ui-remove.sh
</INLINE>
</FILE>

</PLUGIN>
